<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive does not affect the laws of the Member States relating to the use of methanol, propan-1-ol, propan-2-ol and tricholoroethylene as extraction solvents in the production of foodstuffs or food ingredients. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv ei m&otilde;juta neid liikmesriikide &otilde;igusakte, mis k&auml;sitlevad metanooli, propaan-1-ooli, propaan-2-ooli ja trikoloroet&uuml;leeni kasutamist ekstrahentidena toiduainete v&otilde;i toidu koostisosade tootmisel. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) 'solvent' means any substance for dissolving a foodstuff or any component thereof, including any contaminant present in or on that foodstuff; </inglise>
<eesti> a) lahusti - aine, mida kasutatakse toiduaine v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne selle koostisosa, sealhulgas selles toiduaines sisalduvate saasteainete lahustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) 'extraction solvent' means a solvent which is used in an extraction procedure during the processing of raw materials, of foodstuffs, or of components or ingredients of these products and which is removed but which may result in the unintentional, but technically unavoidable, presence of residues or derivatives in the foodstuff or food ingredient. </inglise>
<eesti> b) ekstrahent - lahusti, mida kasutatakse toorainete, toiduainete v&otilde;i nende toodete koostisosade ekstraheerimisel ja mis eemaldatakse, kuid mis v&otilde;ib kaasa tuua tahtmatu, kuid tehniliselt v&auml;ltimatu j&auml;&auml;kainete v&otilde;i derivaatide sisalduse toiduaines v&otilde;i toidu koostisosades. </eesti>
